01/04/2003
DURRES, Albania -- Police said on Monday (31 March) that they had detained a Greek ship and its crew at Durres port on suspicion of involvement in human trafficking. The ship, Anastasios II, docked at the port on Friday. According to police, illegal Pakistani immigrants seized at the border with Greece some days ago arrived in the country aboard it.
In other news Monday, the Albanian and Macedonian armies held a joint military exercise in Krivolak, Macedonia. The exercise was part of what Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski described as strategic co-operation in the area of defence and security. (MIA, ATA - 31/03/03)
